                    "short_description":  "A 17th-18th century palace built by the Travancore Kingdom, famous for its traditional architecture and the massive \u0027Gajendra Moksham\u0027 mural.",
                    "detailed":  "Krishnapuram Palace was built during the reign of Anizham Thirunal Marthanda Varma, the king of the erstwhile Travancore Kingdom, during the 18th century. The palace features traditional Kerala architectural elements including gabled roofs, narrow corridors, and dormer windows. It served as the official residence of the rulers of Kayamkulam when the region was annexed to Travancore. Today, it is maintained as an archaeological museum showcasing royal artifacts, ancient coins, sculptures, weapons, and the renowned \u0027Gajendra Moksham\u0027 mural—one of the largest temple murals in Kerala."
